<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7ab509b7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9712"><num value="9712">§ 9712.</num><heading> Availability to the public of flood-related data</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7ab509b8-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9712/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Administrator shall make flood-related data available to the public on the website of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7ab509b9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9712/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Cost</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Administrator may make the data under subsection (a) freely accessible or available at a cost that does not exceed the cost of preparing the data.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7ab509ba-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/316/s17">Pub. L. 117–316, § 17</ref>, <date date="2022-12-27">Dec. 27, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/4418">136 Stat. 4418</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
